text: The Great Eastern Main Line (also called the East Anglia Main Line) is a main railway line in England. It connects Liverpool Street station in central London with destinations in East London and the East of England. These include Shenfield, Chelmsford, Colchester, , and Norwich. Branch lines connect the main line to Southminster, Braintree, , Harwich, and a number of coastal towns including Southend-on-Sea, Clacton-on-Sea, Walton-on-the-Naze and .National Rail, Rail Services Around London & the South East, (2006) ==References== Category:Railway lines of England Category:Transport in the City of London Category:Transport in the London Borough of Newham Category:Transport in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham Category:Transport in the London Borough of Havering
